The paper deals with path planning, which is a common problem in robotics. The use of RRT* algorithm and its extension RRT* with potential functions are both related to robotics and control systems, which fall under the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of artificial potential field algorithm, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence and control systems, thus making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also deals with optimization and convergence rate, which are topics related to control systems and optimization, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category. The use of simulations and comparisons between different algorithms also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories.
